cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition and hypernymy detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as Bi-GRU and CapsNet suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in information retrieval tasks, indicating that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of capsule networks, which are a relatively new type of neural network, suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
